    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Indian architecture, a complex multi-spired superstructure-type; Anēkāṇḍaka śikhara Variation of spire in Northern Indian temples. One or two rows of half spires are on either side; miniature shikharas adorn the base and corners.</Note_Text>
